    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-07-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-07-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="302" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d302">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Sir F. Bruce</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr. Seward</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-07-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">July</hi> 26, 1865.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Sir Frederick Bruce presents his compliments to Mr. Seward, and begs to
                            enclose a copy of a resolution<note n="*" xml:id="d302fn1">See Appendix,
                                separate volume.</note> passed by the grand division of the Order of
                            the Sons of Temperance of the province of Canada, wherein they offer
                            congratulations on the successful termination of the civil war in this
                            country, and at the same time express their sympathy with the national
                            bereavement.</p>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Horn <hi rend="smallcaps">William H. Seward</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State, Washington.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
